title: Pixel 5 and 4A 5G review: classic Google
description: The Pixel 5 and 4A 5G are Google's flagship phones that aren't technically flagships. They have the classic Google cameras but they also have other "classic" parts like a rear-mounted fingerprint sensor and processor that isn't the fastest you can get. Do they do enough to justify their prices? Dieter Bohn reviews both phones.  If you buy something from a Verge link, Vox Media may earn a commission.
